{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionApplications of large-language models (LLMs) to software coding have reached wide deployment, with examples such as GitHub Copilot [10].",
    "Yet, applications of LLMs to hardware design are still in their infancy [5,7].",
    "Hardware code generation benchmarks have only been available since 2023, including RTLLM [21], VerilogEval [19], VeriGen [29,30], and most recently RTL-Repo [3].",
    "Despite this, LLM model releases have been extremely rapid.",
    "In this work, we survey the progress LLMs have been in the past year by evaluating newer large-language models than those tested in the original VerilogEval paper (published November 2023), including GPT-4o [27] and GPT-4 Turbo [26], open-source models like Llama3.1 [23], and domain-specific models such as RTL-Coder [20]."
  ],
